ce%20comes%20now%20from%20former%20Indian%20diplomat%20D.B.%20Venkatesh%20Varma%20in%20a%20newly%20published%20essay.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EVarma%E2%80%99s%20chapter%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.in%2FIndia-Rising-Scientist-R-Chidambaram-ebook%2Fdp%2FB0CBCHC747%2Fref%3Dtmm_kin_swatch_0%3F_encoding%3DUTF8%26qid%3D1690729129%26sr%3D8-1%5C%22%3ER.%20Chidambaram%E2%80%99s%20recent%20memoir%2C%20%3Cem%3EIndia%20Rising%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20pays%20tribute%20to%20the%20noted%20scientist%E2%80%99s%20role%20in%20shaping%20India%E2%80%99s%20diplomatic%20posture%20on%20nuclear%20issues%20%E2%80%93%20from%20the%20Comprehensive%20Nuclear-Test-Ban%20Treaty%20to%20the%20India-US%20nuclear%20deal%20%E2%80%93%20but%20also%20offers%20a%20glimpse%20of%20the%20divisions%20that%20plagued%20the%20Indian%20side%20as%20the%20US%20made%20demands%20that%20would%20have%20weakened%20India%E2%80%99s%20nuclear%20weapons%20programme.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20243px)%2085vw%2C%20243px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F06171019%2F51NGHvx6qUL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22243%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F06171019%2F51NGHvx6qUL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg%20654w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F06171019%2F51NGHvx6qUL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-196x300.jpg%20196w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-666905%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22372%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ER.%20Chidambaram%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3EIndia%20Rising%3A%20Memoir%20of%20a%20Scientist%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3EPenguin%20eBury%20Press%2C%202023%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20Chidambaram%20was%20the%20principal%20scientific%20adviser%20to%20three%20prime%20ministers%20from%202001%20to%202018%2C%20Varma%20was%20a%20director%20in%20the%20PMO%20for%20the%20crucial%20years%20of%202004-2007%20%E2%80%93%20when%20the%20multi-stage%20nuclear%20deal%20with%20the%20US%20was%20negotiated%20and%20finalised.%20Varma%20subsequently%20became%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fsk-singh-award-for-nuclear-troubleshooter-venkatesh-varma%2Farticle2781321.ece%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20first%20recipient%20of%20the%20S.K.%20Singh%20Award%20for%20Excellence%20in%20the%20Indian%20Foreign%20Service%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20January%202012%20for%20his%20contribution%20to%20negotiating%20the%20India-US%20nuclear%20deal.%20He%20retired%20as%20India%E2%80%99s%20ambassador%20to%20Moscow%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EVarma%E2%80%99s%20chapter%20recounts%20how%20there%20were%20significant%20differences%20among%20the%20DAE%20and%20PMO%20on%20one%20side%2C%20and%20the%20MEA%20on%20the%20other%2C%20during%20various%20stages%20of%20negotiations%20with%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20run-up%20to%20the%20signing%20of%20the%20joint%20statement%20on%20July%2018%2C%202005%2C%20Varma%20writes%20that%20there%20were%20disagreements%20within%20the%20Indian%20delegation%20in%20Washington%20on%20the%20strategic%20price%20that%20India%20should%20willingly%20bear%20in%20exchange%20for%20the%20removal%20of%20international%20trade%20restrictions%20on%20its%20nuclear%20industry%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20were%20already%20a%20lot%20of%20divisions%20on%20the%20Indian%20side%20which%20arose%20from%20the%20fact%20that%20there%20were%20strong%20advocates%20on%20the%20Indian%20side%20willing%20to%20pay%20a%20very%20high%20cost%2C%20almost%20as%20much%20as%20what%20the%20Americans%20wanted%20to%20agree%20to%20the%20nuclear%20deal%2C%20which%20would%20have%20had%20the%20negative%20effect%20of%20emasculating%20our%20nuclear%20weapons%20programme.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20disparity%20was%20evident%20in%20Washington%20on%20the%20eve%20of%20the%20signing%20of%20the%20joint%20statement%2C%20with%20Atomic%20Energy%20Commission%20chairperson%20Anil%20Kakodkar%20%E2%80%9Calmost%20alone%E2%80%9D%20in%20pointing%20out%20the%20pitfalls%20in%20the%20initial%20drafts%20of%20the%20joint%20statement.%20%E2%80%9CHe%20had%20support%20from%20M.K.%20Narayanan%2C%20the%20NSA%20and%20the%20PMO%E2%80%99s%20team.%20But%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20establishment%20were%20saying%20that%20we%20should%20accept%20what%20the%20Americans%20were%20offering%20along%20with%20the%20associated%20high%20costs.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.in%2FFire-Fury-Transforming-Strategic-Identity%2Fdp%2F9353337283%5C%22%3EIn%20his%202019%20book%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20Kakodkar%20gave%20details%20of%20this%20meeting%20chaired%20by%20Manmohan%20Singh%20at%20his%20hotel%20in%20Washington%20on%20the%20eve%20of%20the%20summit.%20He%20specifically%20mentioned%20that%20after%20he%20said%20that%20the%20proposed%20draft%20was%20unacceptable%2C%20%E2%80%9Cseveral%20seniors%E2%80%9D%20had%20%E2%80%9Cpounced%E2%80%9D%20on%20him.%20Kakodkar%20specifically%20named%20Natwar%20Singh%2C%20who%20was%20external%20affairs%20minister%20at%20the%20time%2C%20and%20Indian%20ambassador%20to%20the%20US%20Ronen%20Sen.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWith%20Manmohan%20Singh%20declaring%20that%20Kakodkar%E2%80%99s%20assent%20was%20necessary%20to%20go%20ahead%2C%20the%20final%20draft%20was%20signed%20only%20after%20the%20language%20was%20changed%20as%20per%20the%20latter%E2%80%99s%20formulation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%202005%20joint%20statement%20marked%20the%20start%20of%20three%20years%20of%20tortuous%20negotiations%2C%20as%20India%20drew%20up%20a%20separation%20plan%20for%20its%20civil%20and%20nuclear%20facilities%20and%20consented%20to%20International%20Atomic%20Energy%20Agency%20(IAEA)%20safeguards%20and%20an%20additional%20protocol.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESeparation%20plan%3A%20%E2%80%98Confusion%20on%20the%20Indian%20side%2C%20including%20in%20the%20MEA%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20had%20wanted%20to%20bring%20the%20majority%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20pressurised%20heavy%20water%20reactors%2C%20its%20fast%20breeder%20programme%20and%20part%20of%20the%20Bhabha%20Atomic%20Research%20Centre%20under%20IAEA%20safeguards.%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20Mr%20Kakodkar%20came%20back%20from%20Washington%2C%20he%20realised%20that%20unlike%20in%20the%20past%2C%20the%20times%20had%20changed%2C%20that%20there%20was%20a%20lot%20of%20pressure%20from%20the%20Americans%20and%20other%20western%20countries%20which%20had%20support%20within%20some%20sections%20of%20the%20Indian%20establishment%2C%E2%80%9D%20writes%20Varma.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThough%20Varma%20takes%20no%20names%2C%20the%20MEA%E2%80%99s%20lead%20negotiator%20was%20S.%20Jaishankar%20%E2%80%93%20then%20a%20joint%20secretary%20handling%20the%20US%20and%20Canada%20and%20currently%20India%E2%80%99s%20foreign%20minister%20%E2%80%93%20while%20Shyam%20Saran%20was%20foreign%20secretary.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBased%20on%20his%20suggestion%20to%20NSA%20Narayanan%20that%20there%20be%20an%20internal%20group%20to%20formulate%20a%20unified%20stance%2C%20Varma%20writes%20that%20an%20%E2%80%9Capex%20group%E2%80%9D%20was%20formed%20on%20September%201%2C%202005.%20The%20group%20consisted%20of%20Atomic%20Energy%20Commission%20chair%20Anil%20Kakodkar%2C%20PSA%20R.%20Chidambaram%2C%20PMO%20principal%20secretary%20T.K.%20Nair%2C%20Chief%20of%20Staff%20Committee%20Arun%20Prakash%20and%20joint%20secretary%20PMO%20Sujata%20Mehta.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20was%20the%20need%20to%20establish%20some%20discipline%20of%20what%20the%20negotiating%20brief%20would%20be.%20The%20group%20played%20a%20critical%20role%20in%20the%20negotiation%20of%20the%20nuclear%20deal%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20weeks%20following%20the%20Manmohan-Bush%20joint%20statement%20on%20civilian.%20nuclear%20cooperation%2C%20Varma%20writes%20that%20there%20was%20%E2%80%9Can%20onslaught%20of%20proposals%20from%20the%20US%E2%80%9D%20on%20the%20separation%20plan%20and%20the%20proposed%20123%20agreement.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThough%20Varma%20does%20not%20go%20into%20the%20specifics%2C%20one%20of%20the%20US%20proposals%20that%20the%20MEA%20embraced%20initially%20was%20the%20principle%20of%20%E2%80%98grid%20connectivity%E2%80%99%20as%20basis%20for%20separating%20civilian%20from%20military%20nuclear%20facilities.%20This%20idea%20rang%20alarm%20bells%20in%20the%20DAE%20as%20it%20would%20have%20meant%20the%20bulk%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20nuclear%20reactors%20going%20under%20IAEA%20supervision.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMEA%20officials%20also%20pushed%20the%20narrative%20in%20the%20media%20that%20the%20DAE%E2%80%99s%20insistence%20on%20keeping%20the%20fast-breeder%20programme%20out%20of%20the%20civilian%20list%20would%20make%20the%20US%20drop%20the%20idea%20of%20nuclear%20cooperation%20altogether.%20%E2%80%9CKakodkar%E2%80%99s%20public%20espousal%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Cindigenous%E2%80%9D%20fast%20breeder%20reactors%20remaining%20out%20of%20the%20safeguards%20list%2C%20could%20be%20a%20deal-breaker%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.anilkakodkar.in%2Fkakodkar_media%2Fnews_clips%2Fkakodkar_atomic_energy_chief_muddies_waters_on_n_deal_07022006_2012_08_10_11_22_28_297.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20%3Cem%3ETimes%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%20quoted%20unnamed%20%E2%80%9Csenior%20members%20of%20the%20government%E2%80%9D%20as%20saying%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EReferring%20to%20different%20sections%20in%20the%20Indian%20establishment%20unable%20to%20come%20on%20the%20same%20page%2C%20Varma%20writes%20that%20there%20was%20%E2%80%9Ccomplete%20chaos%20on%20the%20Indian%20side%2C%20with%20the%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20(MEA)%20proceeding%20independently%20on%20its%20own%2C%20while%20the%20DAE%20had%20dif%EF%AC%81culties%20agreeing%20to%20the%20former%E2%80%99s%20approach%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EVarma%20does%20not%20say%20so%20but%20the%20DAE%20managed%20to%20have%20its%20way%20only%20by%20going%20public%20about%20its%20concerns%20in%20an%20interview%20Kakodkar%20gave%20on%20February%206%2C%202006%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0%20much%20to%20the%20consternation%20of%20key%20MEA%20officials%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20interview%20became%20a%20decisive%20factor%20in%20defining%20the%20contours%20of%20the%20Separation%20Plan%2C%E2%80%9D%20R.B.%20Grover%2C%20another%20senior%20DAE%20official%20who%20was%20part%20of%20the%20Indo-US%20negotiations%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2F676782%2Fland-narcotics-trade-and-local-power-dynamics-the-underlying-factors-behind-manipur-chaos%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%20later.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWith%20regard%20to%20other%20aspects%20of%20the%20separation%20plan%2C%20writes%20Varma%2C%20%E2%80%9CConceptual%20clarity%20emerged%20from%20the%20Apex%20Group%20in%20one%20fundamental%20way%20as%20there%20was%20confusion%20on%20the%20Indian%20side%2C%20including%20in%20the%20MEA%2C%20namely%20that%20any%20plant%20that%20produces%20power%20is%20by%20de%EF%AC%81nition%20a%20civilian%20facility.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20Indian%20diplomat%20adds%20that%20the%20US%20had%20%E2%80%9Csent%20signals%E2%80%9D%20that%20it%20would%20not%20accept%20less%20than%2018%20Indian%20reactors%20under%20IAEA%20safeguards%2C%20while%20the%20rest%20would%20be%20enough%20to%20fuel%20the%20nuclear%20weapons%20programme.%20This%20was%20not%20acceptable%20to%20Chidambaram%2C%20who%20asserted%20that%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20nuclear%20weapons%20programme%20and%20its%20requirement%20%E2%80%9Cwere%20entirely%20an%20Indian%20decision%20and%20%EF%AC%81rmly%20rejected%20the%20American%20argument%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWith%20Manmohan%20Singh%20agreeing%20with%20his%20PSA%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthis%20issue%20was%20settled%20once%20and%20for%20all%20by%20early%20February%202006%E2%80%9D.%20Currently%2C%20there%20are%2014%20Indian%20reactors%20under%20IAEA%20safeguards.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Corrective%20measures%E2%80%99%20to%20the%20rescue%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20this%20issue%20was%20crossed%20off%20the%20list%2C%20the%20sticking%20matter%20of%20the%20US%20insistence%20on%20safeguards%20in%20perpetuity%20led%20talks%20between%20the%20Indian%20and%20American%20interlocutors%20breaking%20down%20on%20the%20night%20before%20March%202%2C%20the%20start%20of%20Bush%E2%80%99s%20state%20visit%20to%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20would%20agree%20to%20safeguards%20in%20perpetuity%2C%20but%20the%20key%20issue%20for%20us%2C%20given%20our%20experience%20of%20US-supplied%20reactors%20at%20Tarapur%2C%20was%20whether%20there%20would%20be%20a%20lifetime%20guarantee%20of%20fuel%20supply%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EVarma%20said%20that%20it%20was%20only%20after%20another%20round%20of%20internal%20discussions%20in%20the%20morning%20that%20Kakodkar%20and%20Chidambaram%20worked%20out%20the%20concept%20of%20%E2%80%9Ccorrective%20measures%E2%80%9D.%20As%20per%20this%20construct%2C%20India%20would%20agree%20to%20put%20safeguards%20in%20perpetuity%20and%20US%20would%20agree%20to%20a%20lifetime%20guarantee%20of%20fuel%20supplies.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ERecounting%20his%20conversation%20with%20Chidambaram%20at%20Hyderabad%20House%2C%20Varma%20writes%20that%20he%20assured%20Chidambaram%20that%20the%20drafted%20language%20on%20%E2%80%9Ccorrective%20measures%E2%80%9D%20would%20be%20included%20in%20all%20future%20agreements.%20Following%20this%20assurance%2C%20Chidambaram%20gave%20his%20assent%20to%20the%20separation%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAnd%20the%20promise%20that%20I%20made%20to%20Dr%20Chidambaram%20that%20we%20would%20put%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmea.gov.in%2FUploads%2FPublicationDocs%2F19149_Frequently_Asked_Questions_01-11-2008.pdf%5C%22%3ECorrective%20Measures%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20all%20agreements%20can%20be%20found%20in%20the%20123%20Agreement%2C%20our%20safeguard%20agreements%20and%20Additional%20Protocol%20Agreement.%20It%20is%20quite%20unique%20because%20no%20other%20country%20in%20the%20world%2C%20not%20even%20the%20nuclear%20weapon%20states%2C%20have%20included%20anything%20like%20them%20in%20the%20safeguard%20agreements%2C%E2%80%9D%20Varma%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20side%20was%20not%20entirely%20happy%20with%20the%202006%20Hyde%20Act%20which%20modified%20the%20US%20Atomic%20Energy%20Act%20to%20permit%20nuclear%20cooperation%20with%20India.%20Varma%20reminisces%20that%20in%20a%20meeting%20with%20Manmohan%20Singh%2C%20Chidambaram%20described%20it%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Chideous%20act%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20Hyde%20Act%20having%20many%20%E2%80%9Cinsulting%20provisions%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20%E2%80%98team%E2%80%99%20of%20Chidambaram%20and%20Kakodkar%20decided%20to%20not%20outrightly%20reject%20its%20clauses%2C%20but%20expressed%20strong%20reservations.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EVarma%20wrote%20that%20there%20was%20immense%20pressure%20from%20the%20Americans%20for%20India%20to%20allow%20bilateral%20inspections%20in%20addition%20to%20IAEA%20safeguards%20inspections.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20said%20no.%20He%20(Chidambaram)%20was%20able%20to%20convince%20the%20PM%2C%20who%20made%20a%20statement%20in%20Parliament%2C%20saying%2C%20%E2%80%98I%20do%20not%20wish%20to%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Fpolitics-and-nation%2Fn-button-will-remain-with-us-pm%2Farticleshow%2F1902635.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3EAmerican%20inspectors%3C%2Fa%3E%20roaming%20around%20in%20our%20nuclear%20facilities%E2%80%99.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20Varma%20underlines%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20core%20interests%20were%20largely%20protected%20in%20the%20123%20agreement%2C%20especially%20over%20the%20future%20of%20its%20strategic%20programme.%20%E2%80%9CSo%20today%2C%20we%20have%20a%20nuclear%20deal%20where%20our%20civilian%20programme%20is%20not%20short%20of%20nuclear%20fuel%20and%20our%20weapons%20programme%20is%20proceeding%20merrily%20forward.%20Overall%20it%20has%20been%20a%20success.%20We%20got%20our%20cake%20and%20we%20ate%20it%20too%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695691693000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F26034216%2Fkakodkar-jaishankar-manmohan-bush-chidambaram.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Frevealed-chaos-as-mea-backed-us-demands-in-2005-6-nuclear-talks-dae-pmo-pushback-saved-the-day%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20differences%20within%20the%20Indian%20establishment%2C%20with%20the%20MEA%20apparently%20urging%20accession%20to%20various%20US%20demands%2C%20feature%20in%20a%20recent%20essay%20by%20former%20Indian%20diplomat%20and%20key%20nuclear%20negotiator%2C%20D.B.%20Venkatesh%20Varma.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Frevealed-chaos-as-mea-backed-us-demands-in-2005-6-nuclear-talks-dae-pmo-pushback-saved-the-day%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Inviting%20a%20former%20Nazi%20to%20Zelenskyy's%20speech%20was%20'deeply%20embarrassing'%20to%20all%20Canadians%2C%20Trudeau%20says%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223695%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Rota%20Zelensky%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65122d1382a83a00194b7102%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221847%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Speaker%20of%20the%20House%20of%20Commons%20Anthony%20Rota%20shakes%20hands%20with%20Ukrainian%20President%20Volodymyr%20Zelenskyy%20in%20the%20House%20of%20Commons%20on%20Parliament%20Hill%20in%20Ottawa%20on%20Friday%2C%20Sept.%2022%2C%202023.%20Rota%20is%20apologizing%20for%20recognizing%20in%20Parliament%20a%20man%20who%20fought%20for%20a%20Nazi%20military%20unit%20during%20World%20War%20II%2C%20just%20after%20Zelenskyy%20addressed%20the%20House%20of%20Commons%20on%20Friday.%3Cp%3ESean%20Kilpatrick%2FThe%20Canadian%20Press%20via%20AP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3EPolitical%20pressure%20is%20building%20in%20Canada%20after%20the%20speaker%20of%20the%20House%20of%20Commons%20mistakenly%20honored%20a%20Ukrainian%20Nazi.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EOn%20Monday%2C%20prime%20minister%20Justin%20Trudeau%20called%20the%20ordeal%20%26quot%3Bdeeply%20embarrassing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EStill%2C%20Trudeau%20has%20not%20called%20for%20speaker%20Anthony%20Rota%20to%20resign%2C%20and%20Rota%20is%20also%20resisting%20the%20calls.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ECanadian%20opposition%20parties%20called%20on%20the%20speaker%20of%20the%20House%20of%20Commons%20to%20resign%20Monday%20for%20inviting%20a%20man%20who%20fought%20for%20a%20Nazi%20military%20unit%20during%20World%20War%20II%20to%20attend%20a%20speech%20by%20the%20Ukrainian%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeter%20Julian%2C%20the%20New%20Democratic%20Party%20House%20leader%2C%20and%20Bloc%20Quebecois%20leader%20Yves-Francois%20Blanchet%20both%20said%20Anthony%20Rota%20should%20step%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20the%20good%20of%20the%20institution%20of%20the%20House%20of%20Commons%20...%20I%20don't%20believe%20you%20can%20continue%20in%20this%20role%2C%26quot%3B%20Julian%20said.%20%26quot%3BRegrettably%20I%20must%20respectfully%20ask%20that%20you%20step%20aside.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Moscow%2C%20a%20Kremlin%20spokesman%20said%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Boutrageous%26quot%3B%20that%20Yaroslav%20Hunka%20received%20a%20standing%20ovation%20during%20a%20visit%20to%20Ottawa%20on%20Friday%20by%20Ukrainian%20President%20Volodymyr%20Zelenskyy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20written%20in%20French%2C%20Bloc%20Quebecois%20Leader%20Yves-Francois%20Blanchet%20said%20Rota%20had%20lost%20the%20confidence%20of%20the%20House.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERota%2C%20who%20issued%20a%20written%20apology%20Sunday%20and%20repeated%20it%20in%20the%20House%20on%20Monday%2C%20did%20not%20immediately%20resign.%3Cbr%3EPrime%20Minister%20Justin%20Trudeau%20called%20the%20incident%20%26quot%3Bextremely%20upsetting.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20speaker%20has%20acknowledged%20his%20mistake%20and%20has%20apologized%2C%26quot%3B%20Trudeau%20told%20reporters.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20something%20that%20is%20deeply%20embarrassing%20to%20the%20Parliament%20of%20Canada%20and%20by%20extension%20to%20all%20Canadians.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrudeau's%20office%20and%20their%20shared%20Liberal%20Party%20did%20not%20directly%20call%20for%20Rota%20to%20resign%2C%20although%20political%20pressure%20from%20across%20the%20aisle%20for%20Rota%20to%20resign%20has%20grown.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fworld-us-canada-66919862%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20the%20BBC%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20Trudeau's%20office%20also%20denied%20that%20he%20and%20Rota%20had%20met%20before%20Rota%20made%20the%20decision%20to%20invite%20Hunka.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20apology%2C%20Rota%20said%20he%20alone%20was%20responsible%20for%20inviting%20and%20recognizing%20Hunka.%20%26quot%3BI%20am%20deeply%20sorry%20that%20I%20have%20offended%20many%20with%20my%20gesture%20and%20remarks%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNo%20one%20%E2%80%94%20not%20even%20anyone%20among%20you%2C%20fellow%20parliamentarians%2C%20or%20from%20the%20Ukrainian%20delegation%20%E2%80%94%20was%20privy%20to%20my%20intention%20or%20my%20remarks%20prior%20to%20their%20delivery.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20still%2C%20on%20Monday%2C%20Rota%20refused%20to%20resign%20amid%20the%20backlash%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.com%2Fnews%2F2023%2F09%2F25%2Fcanada-veteran-nazi-ukraine-00118056%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20Politico.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20after%20Zelenskyy%20delivered%20an%20address%20in%20the%20House%20of%20Commons%2C%20Canadian%20lawmakers%20gave%20the%2098-year-old%20Hunka%20a%20standing%20ovation%20when%20Rota%20drew%20attention%20to%20him.%20Rota%20introduced%20Hunka%20as%20a%20war%20hero%20who%20fought%20for%20the%201st%20Ukrainian%20Division.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%201st%20Ukrainian%20Division%20was%20also%20known%20as%20the%20Waffen-SS%20Galicia%20Division%2C%20or%20the%20SS%2014th%20Waffen%20Division%2C%20a%20voluntary%20unit%20that%20was%20under%20the%20command%20of%20the%20Nazis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Friends%20of%20Simon%20Wiesenthal%20Center%20for%20Holocaust%20Studies%20issued%20a%20statement%20Sunday%20saying%20the%20division%20%26quot%3Bwas%20responsible%20for%20the%20mass%20murder%20of%20innocent%20civilians%20with%20a%20level%20of%20brutality%20and%20malice%20that%20is%20unimaginable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECriticism%20also%20grew%20outside%20of%20Canada%2C%20per%20the%20BBC%2C%20with%20Poland's%20ambassador%20to%20Canada%20calling%20for%20an%20apology%20from%20the%20parliament%20for%20%26quot%3Bwhitewashing%20such%20villains%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKremlin%20spokesman%20Dmitry%20Peskov%20said%20memory%20of%20the%20Nazis%20must%20be%20preserved.%20He%20said%20Canada%20is%20among%20the%20Western%20countries%20that%20have%20raised%20a%20young%20generation%20who%20don't%20understand%20the%20threat%20of%20fascism.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSuch%20a%20sloppy%20attitude%20toward%20this%20memory%20is%2C%20of%20course%2C%20outrageous%2C%26quot%3B%20Peskov%20said%20during%20his%20daily%20conference%20call%20with%20reporters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussian%20leader%20Vladimir%20Putin%20has%20painted%20his%20enemies%20in%20Ukraine%20as%20%26quot%3Bneo-Nazis%2C%26quot%3B%20even%20though%20Zelenskyy%20is%20Jewish%20and%20lost%20relatives%20in%20the%20Holocaust.%20In%20his%20apology%2C%20Trudeau%20seemed%20to%20acknowledge%20that%20the%20decision%