ou%20learn%20how%20it%20responds%2C%20how%20it%20understands%20you%2C%20you%20can%20start%20forming%20your%20prompts%20better%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20you're%20always%20going%20to%20be%20tweaking.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20Save%20time%20on%20prep%20work%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESlade%20has%20found%20that%20ChatGPT%20is%20best%20for%20%26quot%3Bprep%20and%20research%2C%26quot%3B%20including%20generating%20topics%20and%20crafting%20outlines%2C%20rather%20than%20writing%20an%20entire%20blog%20article%20or%20social-media%20post.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChatGPT-generated%20content%20is%20often%20expressionless%2C%20too%20literal%2C%20and%20oddly%20worded%2C%20Slade%20added.%20And%20if%20multiple%20people%20are%20entering%20similar%20prompts%2C%20the%20chatbot%20could%20give%20you%20the%20same%20results%20it's%20giving%20others%20and%20you%20might%20end%20up%20with%20a%20blog%20post%20that's%20too%20similar%20to%20a%20competitor's.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe'll%20never%20be%20overly%20reliant%20on%20it%20because%20it%20just%20doesn't%20have%20what%20it%20takes%2C%20which%20is%20humanness%2C%26quot%3B%20Slade%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20Make%20the%20content%20your%20own%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWinfield%20said%20it's%20best%20not%20to%20use%20ChatGPT-produced%20content%20verbatim.%20His%20team%20often%20runs%20the%20copy%20through%20writing%20tools%20like%20Grammarly%20or%20Writesonic%2C%20which%20are%20also%20AI-powered%2C%20to%20spruce%20up%20the%20language.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou'll%20lose%20your%20own%20voice%20that%20makes%20you%20special%20as%20a%20company%20or%20as%20a%20writer%2C%26quot%3B%20Winfield%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20a%20potential%20pitfall.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20chatbot%20can%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-chatbot-chatgpt-google-microsofty-lying-search-belief-2023-2%5C%22%3Eproduce%20incorrect%20information%3C%2Fa%3E.%20If%20you're%20not%20familiar%20with%20the%20su