t%2C%20in%20his%20stylish%20phrasing.)%20Like%20others%20of%20a%20similar%20background%2C%20such%20as%20the%20Sahnis%20and%20the%20Chopras%2C%20his%20brothers%20were%20also%20part%20of%20his%20cultural%20and%20working%20world%2C%20so%20Bhisham%20and%20Balraj%20Sahni%20or%20B.R.%20and%20Yash%20Chopra%2C%20Dev%20Anand%20was%20shaped%20by%20and%20worked%20with%20Chetan%20Anand%20and%20Vijay%20Anand.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDev%20Anand%20has%20talked%20about%20his%20romances%2C%20but%20the%20only%20two%20worth%20mentioning%20here%20are%20his%20famous%20romance%20with%20his%20co-star%20Suraiya%20in%20the%20late%201940s%2C%20something%20he%20himself%20talked%20about%2C%20given%20how%20formational%20she%20was%20to%20his%20career.%20They%20were%20said%20to%20have%20split%20because%20her%20grandmother%20refused%20to%20allow%20her%20to%20marry%20a%20Hindu.%20He%20married%20another%20co-star%2C%20Kalpana%20Kartik%20(Mona%20Singha)%2C%20in%201954%2C%20who%20stepped%20back%20from%20her%20career%20after%20marriage.%20She%20remained%20a%20practising%20Christian%2C%20and%20they%20were%20married%20for%20almost%2060%20years%20until%20his%20death.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDev%20Anand%20worked%20in%20over%20100%20films%2C%20starting%20in%20Prabhat%20Studios%20in%201946%2C%20then%20active%20as%20an%20actor%2C%20producer%2C%20director%2C%20and%20writer%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20his%20life.%20He%20co-founded%20Navketan%20Films%20with%20Chetan%20Anand%20where%20he%20made%20some%20of%20his%20best%20films.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMany%20aspects%20of%20Dev%20Anand%E2%80%99s%20long%20career%20which%20I%20particularly%20enjoyed%20were%20the%20fruit%20of%20his%20working%20with%20other%20talented%20individuals%2C%20including%20some%20of%20the%20great%20female%20stars%20of%20his%20era%2C%20but%20here%20I%20look%20at%20his%20work%20with%20his%20brothers%20and%20others%20at%20Navketan%20Films%20and%20the%20songs%20that%20were%20picturised%20on%20him%20composed%20by%20S.D.%20Burman%20as%20these%20define%20Dev%20Anand.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%201950s%2C%20Dev%20Anand%20was%20in%20several%20films%20which%20define%20the%20style%20of%20%E2%80%98Bombay%20Noir%E2%80%99%2C%20giving%20a%20certain%20grittiness%20in%20the%20depiction%20of%20the%20underworld%20or%20low%20life%20of%20the%20city%20of%20Bombay%2C%20mostly%20at%20night%2C%20which%20nevertheless%20looks%20glamorous%20and%20alluring%20with%20dangerous%20and%20seductive%20women%2C%20often%20vamps%20performing%20in%20nightclubs.%20These%20crime%20thrillers%20often%20feature%20cars%2C%20guns%2C%20phones%20such%20as%20in%20the%20fabulous%20opening%20sequences%20of%20%3Cem%3ECID%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Most%20of%20these%20films%20were%20made%20with%20Navketan%20Films.%20My%20favourites%20include%20those%20directed%20by%20Chetan%20Anand%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DMRWDCx_z-Ns%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ETaxi%20Driver%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%201954)%2C%20Guru%20Dutt%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DXrUsbx8XkHw%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EBaazi%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%201951)%2C%20Vijay%20Anand%20(%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DP_Thh7SiHlY%5C%22%3EKala%20Bazaar%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%201960)%20and%20Raj%20Khosla%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DcQ_tCziP04s%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EKala%20Pani%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%201958).%20Dev%20Anand%20also%20acted%20in%20Guru%20Dutt%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DuOjeDbhbyfw%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EJaal%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20(1952)%20and%20Raj%20Khosla%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DP-WFJ5-Ug3k%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ECID%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20(1956)%2C%20both%20produced%20by%20Guru%20Dutt.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20%3Cem%3ECID%3C%2Fem%3E%20whose%20music%20was%20composed%20by%20O.P.%20Nayyar%2C%20the%20others%20are%20all%20by%20S.D.%20Burman%20and%20are%20some%20of%20the%20most%20loved%20songs%20in%20the%20history%20of%20Hindi%20film%20music.%20While%20Hemant%20Kumar%20sang%20what%20Yash%20Chopra%20called%20his%20favourite%20film%20songs%2C%20Sahir%20Ludhianvi%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3D-6I1JahC6VE%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EYeh%20raat%2C%20yeh%20chandni%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%99%20in%20%3Cem%3EJaal%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20songs%20picturised%20on%20Dev%20Anand%20were%20mostly%20sung%20by%20Mohammed%20Rafi%20and%20Kishore%20Kumar.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2F-6I1JahC6VE%3Fsi%3Dbr22CZH_0i1-qsez%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EAlthough%20Dev%20Anand%E2%80%99s%20songs%20were%20a%20hugely%20important%20part%20of%20his%20star%20persona%2C%20huge%20popularity%20and%20great%20legacy%2C%20he%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20have%20%E2%80%98a%20voice%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20way%20that%20Raj%20Kapoor%20had%20Mukesh%20or%20Amitabh%20had%20Kishore%20Kumar%20but%20is%20closely%20associated%20with%20both%20Rafi%20and%20Kishore.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAgain%2C%20I%20can%E2%80%99t%20choose%20between%20Rafi%20and%20Kishore.%20It%20would%20be%20absurd%20as%20they%20are%20so%20different.%20S.D.%20Burman%20also%20used%20them%20both%20for%20great%20songs.%C2%A0%20However%2C%20S.D.%20Burman%20said%20he%20thought%20Dev%20Anand%20and%20Kishore%20were%20a%20perfect%20match.%20In%20Anirudh%20Bhattacharjee%20and%20Parthiv%20Dhar%E2%80%99s%20recent%20book%2C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.in%2FKishore-Kumar-Biography-Anirudha-Bhattacharjee%2Fdp%2F9356291713%5C%22%3E%20%3Cem%3EKishore%20Kumar%3A%20The%20Ultimate%20Biography%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20S.D.%20Burman%20is%20quoted%20as%20saying%2C%20%E2%80%98Kishore%5B%E2%80%98s%5D%E2%80%A6voice%20was%20born%20for%20the%20actor%E2%80%A6When%20I%20composed%20for%20Dev%2C%20I%20categorically%20tried%20to%20induct%20Kishore.%20Given%20his%20impulsive%20nature%E2%80%A6%5Bhe%5D%20would%20not%20be%20available%20for%20days%20together.%20I%20used%20to%20resort%20to%20Rafi%E2%80%99s%20voice.%E2%80%99%20(p.%20321-2).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDev%20Anand%20and%20Kishore%20also%20had%20a%20great%20rapport%20and%20much%20mutual%20admiration.%20It%20is%20said%20that%20it%20was%20so%20great%20after%20%3Cem%3EBaazi%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20that%20Kishore%20had%20a%20picture%20of%20Dev%20Anand%20on%20his%20wall%20(p.%20165).%20Dev%20Anand%20said%20that%20he%20would%20pay%20Kishore%20as%20much%20as%20he%20received%20for%20a%20film%20as%20he%20found%20that%20Kishore%20could%20get%20his%20style%20just%20right%20(p.189).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fthe-guide-hindi-english-versions%5C%22%3EThe%20Hindi%20%E2%80%98Guide%E2%80%99%20Is%20Audience-Adoring%2C%20but%20Its%20English%20Version%20Is%20Audience-Ignoring%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDev%20Anand%2C%20S.D.%20Burman%20and%20Kishore%20worked%20together%20on%20over%20100%20songs.%20Kishore%20sang%20many%20more%20songs%20for%20Rajesh%20Khanna%20and%20Amitabh%20Bachchan%20but%20they%20were%20usually%20with%20R.D.%20Burman.%20I%20suggest%20that%20the%20romantic%20persona%20of%20Dev%20Anand%20was%20the%20source%20of%20the%20middle%20class%20romantic%20hero%20that%20Rajesh%20Khanna%20took%20in%20the%20late%201960s%2C%20another%20non-dancing%20hero%20with%20much%20imitated%20facial%20expressions%20and%20a%20sense%20of%20style.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20this%20period%20of%20Dev%20Anand%E2%80%99s%20work%20that%20I%20liked%20most.%20Although%20I%20watched%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3D8n0qIz1oBmg%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EJoshila%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20(1973)%20when%20I%20was%20working%20on%20Yash%20Chopra%2C%20it%20is%20not%20memorable.%20Dev%20Anand%E2%80%99s%20directorial%20film%2C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DIAnJk1lQUqQ%5C%22%3E%20%3Cem%3EPrem%20Pujari%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3C%2Fa%3E(1970)%20had%20some%20massive%20hits%20by%20S.D.%20Burman%20sung%20by%20Kishore%3A%20%E2%80%99%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DlZ4hoCYKKM4%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EShokhiyon%20mein%20ghol%3C%2Fem%3Ea%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%98%20and%20%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3D4CwFFWleNNA%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EPhoolon%20ke%20rang%20se%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%99.%20The%20last%20Dev%20Anand%20film%20I%20saw%20was%20the%20hippy%20classic%2C%20%3Cem%3EHare%20Rama%20Hare%20Krishna%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1971).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAbove%20all%20I%20think%20of%20Dev%20Anand%20from%20the%201950s%20and%201960s%2C%20when%20he%20gave%20great%20performances%20in%20outstanding%20films%20with%20memorable%20songs%20by%20S.D.%20Burman%2C%20sung%20by%20Kishore%20Kumar.%20This%20is%20how%20I%20will%20always%20remember%20and%20cherish%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHappy%20Birthday%2C%20Dev%20Saab.%20Stay%20forever%20young.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Frachel%5C%22%3ERachel%20Dwyer%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20professor%20emerita%20of%20Indian%20culture%20and%20cinema%20at%20SOAS%2C%20University%20of%20London.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695645058000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25164355%2Fimage-1352.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fdev-anand-was-a-stylish-icon-of-hindi-cinema-who-reflected-indian-modernity%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20tribute%20to%20the%20star%20who%20gave%20us%20some%20great%20films%2C%20on%20the%20occasion%20of%20his%20100th%20anniversary.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A23%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fdev-anand-was-a-stylish-icon-of-hindi-cinema-who-reflected-indian-modernity%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Herd%20of%20sheep