%22%3A%22Periyar%20Lalai%20Baudh%3A%20The%20Unsung%20Hero%20of%20the%20Anti-Caste%20Movement%20in%20North%20India%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25145950%2F20230902_233611.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPeriyar%20Lalai%20Baudh%20was%20a%20policeman%2C%20a%20playwright%2C%20a%20translator%2C%20a%20publisher%2C%20and%20above%20all%2C%20a%20fierce%20anti-caste%20activist%20who%20dedicated%20his%20life%20to%20spreading%20the%20message%20of%20Ambedkarism%2C%20Periyarism%20and%20Buddhism%20among%20the%20oppressed%20north%20India.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPeriyar%20Lalai%20Baudh%20was%20born%20on%20September%201%2C%201911%2C%20in%20Kathara%20village%20near%20Jhinjhak%20railway%20station%20in%20Kanpur%20Dehat%20district%20of%20Uttar%20Pradesh.%20He%20belonged%20to%20the%20Yadav%20community%2C%20classified%20as%20an%20Other%20Backward%20Class%20(OBC)%20in%20India.%20He%20received%20his%20primary%20education%20in%20his%20village%20and%20later%20joined%20the%20armed%20police%20force%20of%20Gwalior%20state%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20in%201933%20as%20a%20constable.%20However%2C%20he%20was%20dismissed%20after%20two%20years%20for%20supporting%20the%20Congress%20party%E2%80%99s%20struggle%20for%20independence%2C%20which%20was%20considered%20a%20crime%20by%20the%20British%20government.%20He%20appealed%20against%20his%20dismissal%20and%20was%20reinstated%20later.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20founded%20the%20Non-Gazetted%20Employees%20Union%20of%20Police%20and%20Army%20in%20Gwalior%20in%201946%20to%20raise%20the%20issues%20of%20police%20personnel%20facing%20exploitation%20and%20discrimination%20by%20the%20higher%20authorities.%20He%20also%20wrote%20a%20book%20titled%20%3Cem%3ESipahi%20Ki%20Tabahi%3C%2Fem%3E%20(%E2%80%98The%20Destruction%20of%20a%20Soldier%E2%80%99)%20in%201946%2C%20which%20exposed%20the%20corruption%20and%20oppression%20in%20the%20British%20police%20and%20army.%20The%20book%20was%20not%20published%20but%20was%20typed%20and%20distributed%20among%20soldiers.%20However%2C%20it%20was%20confiscated%20by%20the%20Inspector%20General%20of%20the%20Army%20when%20he%20came%20to%20know%20about%20it.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20same%20year%2C%20he%20also%20organised%20a%20strike%20among%20the%20ranks%20of%20the%20Gwalior%20police%20and%20army%2C%20demanding%20better%20wages%20and%20working%20conditions.%20He%20was%20arrested%20on%20March%2029%2C%201947%2C%20and%20charged%20with%20sedition%20and%20conspiracy.%20He%20was%20sentenced%20to%20five%20years%20of%20rigorous%20imprisonment.%20He%20spent%20nine%20months%20in%20jail%20until%20he%20was%20released%20on%20January%2012%2C%201948%2C%20after%20India%E2%80%99s%20independence%20and%20the%20merger%20of%20Gwalior%20state%20with%20the%20Indian%20Union.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEncounter%20with%20Ambedkarism%20and%20Periyarism%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPeriyar%20Lalai%E2%80%99s%20life%20changed%20when%20he%20came%20across%20the%20writings%20and%20speeches%20of%20Dr.%20B.R.%20Ambedkar%2C%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20Dalit%20movement%20and%20the%20chief%20architect%20of%20the%20Indian%20constitution.%20He%20was%20deeply%20impressed%20by%20Ambedkar%E2%80%99s%20analysis%20of%20caste%2C%20religion%2C%20democracy%2C%20and%20human%20rights.%20He%20became%20an%20ardent%20follower%20of%20Ambedkar%20and%20started%20propagating%20his%20ideas%20among%20his%20fellow%20policemen%20and%20villagers.%20He%20also%20joined%20the%20Scheduled%20Castes%20Federation%20(SCF)%2C%20the%20political%20party%20founded%20by%20Ambedkar%20in%201942.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPeriyar%20Lalai%20Baudh%20also%20eventually%20learned%20about%20Periyar%20E.V.%20Ramasamy%2C%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20Dravidian%20movement%20and%20the%20founder%20of%20the%20Self-Respect%20Movement%20in%20South%20India.%20He%20was%20inspired%20by%20Periyar%E2%80%99s%20critique%20of%20Brahminism%2C%20Hinduism%2C%20and%20Aryanism.%20He%20admired%20Periyar%E2%80%99s%20rationalism%2C%20atheism%2C%20feminism%2C%20and%20social%20justice%20agenda%20and%20decided%20to%20translate%20Periyar%E2%80%99s%20works%20from%20Tamil%20to%20Hindi%20to%20make%20them%20accessible%20to%20the%20north%20Indian%20audience.%20He%20translated%20Periyar%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Key%20To%20Understanding%20True%20Ramayan%3C%2Fem%3E%20as%20%3Cem%3ESachi%20Ramayan%20Ki%20Chabi%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%201959.%20This%20book%20exposed%20the%20Brahminical%20distortions%20and%20fabrications%20in%20the%20Ramayana%20and%20presented%20Rama%20as%20a%20villain%20and%20Ravana%20as%20a%20hero.%20It%20also%20questioned%20the%20authority%20and%20authenticity%20of%20the%20Vedas%2C%20Puranas%2C%20Smritis%2C%20and%20other%20Hindu%20scriptures.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20is%20well%20known%2C%20Ambedkarism%20and%20Periyarism%20are%20social%20and%20political%20philosophies%20that%20emerged%20in%20India%20in%20the%2020th%20century.%20They%20are%20named%20after%20their%20respective%20founders%2C%20Dr.%20B.R.%20Ambedkar%20and%20E.V.%20Ramasamy%20Periyar.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fperiyar-ev-ramasamy-dravida-nadu-brahmins-dmk%5C%22%3EWhy%20Do%20Dravidian%20Intellectuals%20Admire%20a%20Man%20as%20Prickly%20as%20Periyar%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBoth%20Ambedkarism%20and%20Periyarism%20are%20based%20on%20the%20principles%20of%20equality%2C%20liberty%2C%20fraternity%2C%20and%20dignity%20for%20all%20human%20beings.%20They%20both%20reject%20the%20authority%20and%20authenticity%20of%20the%20Hindu%20scriptures%20that%20justify%20the%20caste%20system%20and%20its%20associated%20practices%2C%20such%20as%20untouchability%2C%20endogamy%2C%20and%20ritual%20pollution.%20They%20both%20advocate%20for%20the%20emancipation%20of%20the%20socially%20oppressed%20by%20abolishing%20Hinduism%20and%20adopting%20alternative%20religions%20or%20ideologies%20that%20respect%20human%20rights%20and%20values.%20They%20both%20strive%20for%20political%20empowerment%20and%20representation%20of%20the%20marginalized%20sections%20of%20society%20through%20democratic%20means.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESocial%20activism%20and%20struggles%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPeriyar%20Lalai%E2%80%99s%20translation%20of%20Periyar%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3ETrue%20Ramayan%3C%2Fem%3E%20created%20a%20massive%20uproar%20among%20the%20Hindu%20fundamentalists%20and%20%E2%80%98upper%E2%80%99%20castes.%20They%20accused%20him%20of%20hurting%20their%20religious%20sentiments%20and%20demanded%20a%20ban%20on%20his%20book.%20They%20also%20filed%20a%20case%20against%20him%20under%20Section%20295A%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20(IPC)%2C%20which%20deals%20with%20deliberate%20and%20malicious%20acts%20intended%20to%20outrage%20religious%20feelings.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPeriyar%20Lalai%20faced%20harassment%2C%20threats%2C%20and%20violence%20from%20his%20opponents.%20His%20printing%20press%20was%20attacked%2C%20and%20the%20police%20confiscated%20his%20books.%20He%20had%20to%20fight%20a%20long%20legal%20battle%20to%20defend%20his%20right%20to%20free%20speech%20and%20expression.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20also%20faced%20opposition%20from%20some%20of%20his%20caste%20fellows%20loyal%20to%20the%20Congress%20party.%20He%20was%20critical%20of%20Bahujan%20leaders%20for%20being%20a%20puppet%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98upper%E2%80%99%20castes%20and%20for%20betraying%20the%20cause%20of%20the%20oppressed%20masses.%20He%20also%20denounced%20Bahujan%20leaders%20like%20Ramdhan%20Pasi%20and%20Motiram%20Kori%20for%20being%20subservient%20to%20Brahminism%20and%20urged%20the%20Dalits%20and%20OBCs%20to%20unite%20under%20Ambedkarism%20and%20Periyarism.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELiterary%20and%20cultural%20contributions%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPeriyar%20Lalai%20was%20a%20prolific%20writer.%20However%2C%20he%20wrote%20everything%20intending%20to%20raise%20anti-caste%20consciousness%20among%20the%20masses.%20He%20was%20one%20of%20the%20first%20ones%20to%20publish%20Ambedkar%E2%80%99s%20speeches%20in%20Hindi%20and%20ran%20printing%20presses%20such%20as%20Ashok%20Press%2C%20Sasta%20Press%2C%20and%20Periyar%20Press.%20He%20published%20books%2C%20pamphlets%2C%20magazines%2C%20and%20newspapers%20on%20various%20topics%20related%20to%20caste%2C%20religion%2C%20politics%2C%20economics%2C%20history%2C%20culture%2C%20and%20education.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESome%20of%20his%20notable%20publications%20are%3A%20%3Cem%3EBaman%20Vadi%20Rajya%20Mein%20Shoshito%20Par%20Rajnaitik%20Dakaiti%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1962)%2C%20a%20book%20on%20the%20political%20and%20economic%20exploitation%20of%20the%20oppressed%20by%20the%20Brahminical%20state.%20%3Cem%3EBuddha%20Ki%20Drishti%20Mein%20Ishwar%2C%20Brahma%20Aur%20Atma%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1978)%20is%20a%20book%20on%20the%20Buddhist%20philosophy%20of%20no%20god%2C%20no%20soul%2C%20and%20no%20self.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fambedkar-jayanti-untouchability%5C%22%3EWhile%20Celebrating%20Ambedkar%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98National%20Hero%E2%80%99%2C%20We%20Must%20Not%20Forget%20His%20Central%20Thesis%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3EDr.%20Ambedkar%20Boudhha%20Kyon%20Bane%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1978)%2C%20a%20book%20on%20the%20reasons%20and%20significance%20of%20Ambedkar%E2%80%99s%20conversion%20to%20Buddhism.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20play%20%3Cem%3EShanbhuk%20Vadh%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1964)%20is%20based%20on%20the%20myth%20of%20Sambuk%E2%80%99s%20murder.%20It%20is%20a%20story%20that%20is%20found%20in%20the%20Uttara%20Kanda%3B%20according%20to%20this%20story%2C%20Rama%2C%20the%20king%20of%20Ayodhya%2C%20killed%20a%20shudra%20ascetic%20named%20Shambuka%20for%20performing%20%3Cem%3Etapas%3C%2Fem%3E%20(austerities)%2C%20which%20was%20against%20the%20rules%20of%20%3Cem%3Edharma%3C%2Fem%3E%20(duty)%20for%20his%20caste.%20This%20act%20of%20Rama%20was%20supposed%20to%20restore%20the%20balance%20of%20the%20cosmic%20order%20and%20revive%20a%20Brahmin%20son%20who%20had%20died%20due%20to%20Shambuka%E2%80%99s%20transgression.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20this%20story%20has%20been%20criticised%20and%20rejected%20by%20many%20scholars%20and%20thinkers%20as%20an%20interpolation%20and%20a%20fabrication%20that%20was%20created%20to%20justify%20the%20caste%20system%20and%20Brahminical%20domination.%20Some%20of%20the%20prominent%20critics%20of%20this%20story%20are%20Rabindranath%20Tagore%2C%20B.R.%20Ambedkar%2C%20and%20Kuvempu.%20They%20have%20challenged%20the%20validity%20and%20morality%20of%20this%20story%20and%20have%20offered%20alternative%20interpretations%20and%20perspectives%20on%20it.%20They%20have%20also%20used%20this%20story%20as%20a%20basis%20for%20their%20critique%20of%20Brahmanism%20and%20the%20Varna%20system.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20play%20%3Cem%3EEklavya%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1965)%20is%20on%20the%20famous%20myth%20of%20Eklavya.%20It%20is%20a%20story%20from%20the%20Indian%20epic%20%3Cem%3EMahabharata%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20tells%20the%20tale%20of%20a%20young%20tribal%20prince%20who%20aspired%20to%20become%20an%20archer%20under%20the%20guidance%20of%20Guru%20Dronacharya%2C%20the%20royal%20teacher%20of%20the%20Kuru%20princes.%20However%2C%20he%20was%20rejected%20by%20the%20Guru%20because%20of%20his%20low%20caste%20and%20social%20status.%20Undeterred%2C%20Eklavya%20made%20a%20clay%20statue%20of%20Dronacharya%20and%20practiced%20archery%20in%20front%20of%20it%2C%20considering%20the%20statue%20as%20his%20Guru.%20He%20became%20so%20skilled%20that%20he%20surpassed%20Arjuna%2C%20the%20best%20archer%20among%20the%20Kuru%20princes%20and%20the%20favorite%20student%20of%20Dronacharya.%20When%20Dronacharya%20learned%20of%20this%2C%20he%20asked%20Eklavya%20to%20give%20him%20his%20right%20thumb%20as%20a%20%3Cem%3EGuru%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EDakshina%3C%2Fem%3E%20(a%20gift%20of%20gratitude%20to%20the%20teacher)%2C%20knowing%20it%20would%20cripple%20his%20archery.%20Eklavya%2C%20out%20of%20devotion%20and%20respect%2C%20willingly%20cut%20off%20his%20thumb%20and%20offered%20it%20to%20Dronacharya.%20The%20story%20of%20Eklavya%20is%20often%20seen%20as%20an%20example%20of%20loyalty%2C%20sacrifice%2C%20and%20self-learning.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPeriyar%20Lalai%20viewed%20Eklavya%E2%80%99s%20story%20as%20a%20tragedy%20of%20social%20injustice%20and%20discrimination.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20play%20%3Cem%3EAngulimala%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1966)%20is%20based%20on%20the%20myth%20of%20Angulimal.%20It%20is%20a%20story%20from%20the%20Buddhist%20scriptures%20of%20a%20blood-thirsty%20murderer%20who%20lived%20when%20the%20Buddha%20walked%20the%20earth.%20He%20was%20known%20for%20the%20garland%20of%20fingers%20he%20severed%20from%20his%20victims%20and%20wore%20around%20his%20neck.%20His%20name%20means%20%E2%80%9Cfinger%20necklace%E2%80%9D%20in%20Pali.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20was%20initially%20a%20brilliant%20student%20named%20Ahimsaka%2C%20but%20his%20jealous%20classmates%20tricked%20him%20into%20believing%20he%20had%20to%20collect%20a%20thousand%20human%20fingers%20to%20graduate%20from%20his%20teacher.%20He%20became%20a%20ruthless%20killer%2C%20terrorising%20the%20people%20and%20the%20king.%20He%20encountered%20the%20Buddha%20when%20he%20collected%20most%20of%20the%20fingers%20and%20decided%20to%20make%20Buddha%20his%20final%20victim.%20However%2C%20he%20could%20not%20catch%20up%20with%20the%20Buddha%2C%20who%20calmly%20told%20him%20to%20stop%20harming%20others.%20The%20Buddha%E2%80%99s%20words%20moved%20Angulimal%2C%20and%20threw%20away%20his%20weapons%2C%20following%20him%20to%20the%20monastery%2C%20where%20he%20became%20a%20monk.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%C2%A0%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22What%20Dr%20Ambedkar%E2%80%99s%20'Who%20Were%20the%20Shudras%3F'%20Tells%20Us%20About%20the%20Sacred%20Books%20of%20Hinduism%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fdr-ambedkar-who-were-the-shudras-hinduism%5C%22%3EWhat%20Dr%20Ambedkar%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98Who%20Were%20the%20Shudras%3F%E2%80%99%20Tells%20Us%20About%20the%20Sacred%20Books%20of%20Hinduism%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20faced%20many%20difficulties%20and%20dangers%20as%20a%20monk%2C%20as%20people%20still%20hated%20him%20for%20his%20past%20deeds.%20He%20also%20had%20to%20endure%20the%20consequences%20of%20his%20actions%2C%20such%20as%20being%20stoned%20and%20beaten%20by%20angry%20mobs.%20However%2C%20he%20remained%20patient%20and%20faithful%20to%20the%20Buddha%E2%80%99s%20teachings%20and%20eventually%20attained%20enlightenment.%20Buddhists%20see%20him%20as%20a%20symbol%20of%20spiritual%20transformation%20and%20the%20power%20of%20compassion.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EApart%20from%20these%20plays%2C%20Periyar%20Lalai%20also%20wrote%20poems%2C%20songs%2C%20slogans%2C%20and%20dialogues%20to%20inspire%20and%20mobilise%20the%20masses.%20He%20used%20simple%20and%20colloquial%20language%20to%20communicate%20his%20message%20effectively.%20He%20also%20organised%20cultural%20programmes%2C%20rallies%2C%20conferences%2C%20and%20camps%20to%20spread%20awareness%20and%20education%20among%20the%20people.%20He%20invited%20prominent%20leaders%20and%20thinkers%20like%20Dalai%20Lama%2C%20A.R.%20Akela%2C%20Ramswaroop%20Verma%2C%20Kanshi%20Ram%2C%20and%20others%20to%20address%20his%20gatherings.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EConversion%20to%20Buddhism%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPeriyar%20Lalai%20was%20an%20Ambedkarite%20Buddhist%20who%20renounced%20Hinduism%20and%20embraced%20Buddhism%20in%201967%2C%20along%20with%20thousands%20of%20other%20Dalits%20and%20OBCs.%20Following%20Ambedkar%2C%20he%20adopted%20Buddhism%20as%20a%20way%20of%20life%20that%20offered%20equality%2C%20liberty%2C%20fraternity%2C%20and%20dignity%20to%20all%20human%20beings.%20He%20removed%20the%20word%20%E2%80%98Yadav%E2%80%99%20from%20his%20name%20and%20replaced%20it%20with%20Baudh%20(Buddhist).%20He%20did%20this%20to%20express%20his%20rejection%20of%20caste%20identity%20and%20his%20affirmation%20of%20human%20identity.%20He%20also%20wanted%20to%20inspire%20others%20to%20do%20the%20same.%20He%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CI%20am%20not%20a%20Yadav.%20I%20am%20a%20human%20being.%20I%20am%20a%20Buddhist.%20I%20have%20no%20caste.%20I%20have%20no%20religion.%20I%20have%20only%20one%20dharma%20%E2%80%93%20humanity.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20wrote%20extensively%20on%20Buddhism.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPeriyar%20Lalai%20died%20on%20February%207%2C%201993%20at%20the%20age%20of%2081.%20He%20left%20behind%20a%20rich%20legacy%20of%20anti-caste%20literature%20and%20activism%20that%20inspired%20generations%20of%20Dalits%2C%20OBCs%2C%20and%20other%20marginalised%20groups%20in%20north%20India.%20He%20was%20one%20of%20the%20pioneers%20of%20the%20Bahujan%20movement%20that%20sought%20to%20unite%20all%20oppressed%20castes%20under%20a%20common%20identity%20and%20agenda.%20He%20was%20also%20one%20of%20the%20unsung%20heroes%20of%20the%20Dalit-Bahujan%20literature%20that%20challenged%20the%20hegemony%20of%20Brahminical%20literature%20and%20culture.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPeriyar%20Lalai%E2%80%99s%20life%20and%20work%20are%20still%20relevant%20today%20as%20India%20continues%20to%20grapple%20with%20the%20issues%20of%20caste%20discrimination%2C%20religious%20intolerance%2C%20social%20injustice%2C%20and%20human%20rights%20violations.%20His%20writings%20and%20speeches%20provide%20a%20powerful%20critique%20of%20Brahmanism%20and%20Hindutva%20and%20a%20positive%20vision%20of%20an%20egalitarian%20and%20democratic%20society%20based%20on%20Ambedkarism%2C%20Periyarism%2C%20and%20Buddhism.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPeriyar%20Lalai%20deserves%20more%20recognition%20and%20appreciation%20for%20his%20courageous%20and%20creative%20contributions%20to%20the%20anti-caste%20movement%20in%20North%20India.%20He%20should%20be%20remembered%20as%20a%20true%20Periyarist%20and%20follower%20of%20Periyar%E2%80%99s%20motto%3A%20%E2%80%9CBe%20not%20afraid%3B%20Be%20not%20ashamed.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDr%20Sandeep%20Yadav%20is%20a%20University%20Gold%20Medalist%20in%20PG.%20He%20has%20been%20teaching%20english%20as%20an%20Associate%20Professor%20in%20SLC(E)%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Delhi%20for%20the%20last%2015%20years.%20He%20has%20been%20a%20permanent%20faculty%20member%20at%20the%20Central%20University%20of%20Jharkhand%20for%20four%20years.%20He%20has%20published%20many%20books%2C%20among%20which%20%E0%A4%93%E0%A4%AC%E0%A5%80%E0%A4%B8%E0%A5%80%20%E0%A4%94%E0%A4%B0%20%E0%A4%AD%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%A4%20has%20a%20consistent%20best%20seller.%20Yadav%20is%20a%20social%20activist.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695634295000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25145950%2F20230902_233611.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fperiyar-lalai-baudh-the-unsung-hero-of-the-anti-caste-movement-in-north-india%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20true%20Ambedkarite%20and%20Periyarist%2C%20his%20work%2C%20activism%20and%20translations%20are%20priceless%20in%20India's%20equality%20movement.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A18%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fperiyar-lalai-baudh-the-unsung-hero-of-the-anti-caste-movement-in-north-india%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Pushed%20to%20the%20Limit%3A%20The%20Working%20Lives%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20Freight%20Train%20Drivers%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25131942%2F288A2416.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EOn%20June%202%2C%202023%2C%20288%20people%20were%20killed%20in%20a%20railway%20crash%20near%20Bahanaga%20Bazaar%20Railway%20Station%20in%20Odisha%2C%20making%20this%20India%E2%80%99s%20worst%20train%20accident%20since%201995.%20The%20discussion%20on%20railway%20safety%20this%20has%20provoked%20has%20largely%20ignored%20the%20working%20conditions%20of%20railway%20workers%2C%20perhaps%20the%20largest%20public-sector%20workforce%20in%20the%20country.%20The%20following%20two%20articles%20consider%20the%20working%20conditions%20of%20railway%20train%20drivers%2C%20known%20in%20the%20Indian%20Railways%20as%20%E2%80%98loco%20pilots%E2%80%99%20(LPs)%2C%20particularly%20freight%20or%20goods%20LPs%20who%20constitute%20roughly%2070%25%20of%20the%20total%20LPs%20in%20the%20country.%20The%20information%20for%20these%20articles%20was%20collected%20through%20interviews%20with%20members%20of%20the%20Loco%20Running%20Staff%20Association%20(LRSA)%2C%20a%20trade%20union%20of%20approximately%2044%2C000%20railway%20running%20staff.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20first%20article%20looks%20at%20LPs%E2%80%99%20lengthening%20working%20hours%2C%20shrinking%20rest%20periods%2C%20and%20the%20impact%20this%20has%20on%20railway%20accidents.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20India%20faces%20a%20severe%20unemployment%20crisis.%20Yet%2C%20state-sector%20jobs%20are%20being%20cut%20in%20large%20numbers%2C%20deepening%20this%20crisis%20%E2%80%93%20particularly%20in%20the%20railways%2C%20perhaps%20India%E2%80%99s%20largest%20formal-sector%20industrial%20employer.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHere%2C%20the%20scale%20of%20the%20problem%20is%20larger%20than%20commonly%20stated.%20Railway%20minister%20Ashwini%20Vaishnav%20said%20on%20February%203%2C%202023%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20that%20there%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.staffnews.in%2F2023%2F02%2Fstaff-shortage-in-railways-details-of-gazetted-and-non-gazetted-vacancies.html%5C%22%3Ealmost%203.15%20lakh%3C%2Fa%3E%20vacant%20posts%20out%20of%20the%20total%20sanctioned%20strength%20of%20the%20railway%20workforce.%20But%20this%20figure%2C%20alarming%20as%20it%20is%2C%20does%20not%20give%20us%20a%20true%20picture%20of%20the%20manpower%20crisis%20in%20the%20network.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Railway%20Board%20has%20been%20reducing%20the%20total%20number%20of%20sanctioned%20posts%20(known%20as%20%E2%80%9Csurrendering%E2%80%9D)%20in%20the%20railways%20over%20the%20years%2C%20without%20proper%20concerns%20for%20the%20operational%20needs%20of%20the%20system.%20In%202014%2C%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffrontline.thehindu.com%2Fthe-nation%2Fpoor-track-record%2Farticle6100452.ece%3Fart%3Dpackage%5C%22%3EFrontline%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%20that%20a%20government%20order%20circulated%20by%20the%20Railways%20said%20that%20no%20post%20that%20had%20been%20vacant%20for%20a%20year%20or%20more%20should%20be%20revived%20and%20no%20new%20post%20should%20be%20created.%20The%20article%20quoted%20A.K.%20Padmanabhan%20of%20the%20Centre%20of%20Indian%20Trade%20Unions%20as%20saying%3A%20%E2%80%9CThey%20don%E2%80%99t%20hire%20people%20and%20then%20abolish%20the%20post%20saying%20that%20it%20has%20been%20vacant%20for%20a%20long%20time.%E2%80%9D%20The%20LRSA%20claimed%20in%20a%20press%20release%20dated%20March%2022%2C%202023%20that%20in%20the%20Covid%20period%20no%20less%20than%2080%2C000%20sanctioned%20railway%20posts%20were%20surrendered.%20In%20recent%20instances%2C%20Group%20D%20workers%20of%20the%20Central%20Railways%20have%20found%20that%20examinations%20for%20positions%20they%20have%20been%20preparing%20for%20since%202019%20have%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faifap.org.in%2F9997%2F%5C%22%3Esurrendered%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20and%20the%20general%20manager%2C%20South%20Central%20Railways%2C%20has%20issued%20a%20letter%20on%20August%2021%2C%202023%20claiming%202%2C195%20more%20posts%20are%20to%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faifap.org.in%2F10124%2F%5C%22%3Esurrendered%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20perhaps%20more%20instructive%20to%20consider%20the%20absolute%20decline%20in%20the%20size%20of%20the%20railway%20workforce%20over%20the%20past%20decades.%20According%20to%20railway%20ministry%20statistics%2C%20there%20has%20been%20a%20consistent%20decline%20in%20the%20number%20of%20railway%20workers%20since%20at%20least%201991%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ctable%3E%20%3Ctbody%3E%20%3Ctr%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22199%5C%22%3EYear%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22214%5C%22%3ENumber%20of%20railway%20employees%20(in%20lakhs)%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22188%5C%22%3ELoss%20of%20railway%20jobs%20%3Cp%3E(in%20lakhs)%20%20%3Ctr%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22199%5C%22%3E1990-1991%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22214%5C%22%3E16.52%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22188%5C%22%3EN%2FA%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3C%2Ftr%3E%20%3Ctr%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22199%5C%22%3E2000-2001%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22214%5C%22%3E15.45%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22188%5C%22%3E%E2%80%93%201.07%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3C%2Ftr%3E%20%3Ctr%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22199%5C%22%3E2010-2011%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22214%5C%22%3E13.32%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22188%5C%22%3E%E2%80%93%202.13%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3C%2Ftr%3E%20%3Ctr%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22199%5C%22%3E2021-2022%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22214%5C%22%3E12.12%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22188%5C%22%3E%E2%80%93%201.20%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3C%2Ftr%3E%20%3Ctr%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22199%5C%22%3ETotal%20decline%20from%201991-2022%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22214%5C%22%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22188%5C%22%3E%E2%80%93%204.40%3C%2Ftd%3E%20%3C%2Ftr%3E%20%20%20%3Cp%3ESource%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Firitm.indianrailways.gov.in%2Fuploads%2Ffiles%2F1680252282408-PDF%2520Year%2520Book%25202021-22-English.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ERailway%20Year%20Book%202021-2022%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThat%20is%20to%20say%2C%20over%20the%20past%2031%20years%2C%20%3Cem%3Emore%20than%20a%20quarter%20of%20the%20workforce%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20or%204.4%20lakh%20jobs%2C%20have%20been%20cut%20in%20the%20railways.%20And%20this%20has%20come%20at%20a%20time%20when%20the%20manpower%20requirements%20of%20the%20railways%20have%20often%20%3Cem%3Eincreased%20%3C%2Fem%3Erather%20than%20decreased.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Firitm.indianrailways.gov.in%2Fuploads%2Ffiles%2F1680252282408-PDF%2520Year%2520Book%25202021-22-English.pdf%5C%22%3EIn%20the%20same%20period%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20total%20track%20length%20increased%20by%20almost%2018%25%2C%20the%20number%20of%20coaches%20by%2021%25%20and%20the%20number%20of%20locomotives%20by%2057%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20discrepancy%20is%20especially%20sharp%20if%20seen%20from%20the%20point%20of%20view%20of%20LPs.%20From%201991%20to%202012%2C%20as%20the%20railway%20workforce%20was%20slashed%20by%203.2%20lakhs%2C%20the%20number%20of%20trains%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffrontline.thehindu.com%2Fthe-nation%2Farticle30167487.ece%3Fart%3Dpackage%5C%22%3Eincreased%3C%2Fa%3E%20fourfold%20and%20often%20their%20speed%20doubled.%20Moreover%2C%20as%20the%20railway%20ministry%E2%80%99s%202013%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Failrsa.com%2Fassets%2Fdocuments%2Fhpc_report_2.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EReport%20of%20High%20Power%20Committee%20to%20Review%20the%20Duty%20Hours%20of%20Running%20and%20other%20Safety%20Related%20Categories%20of%20Staff%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20(HPC)%20put%20it%2C%20for%20running%20staff%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20stress%20levels%20have%20apparently%20gone%20up%20many%20times%20due%20to%20higher%20speeds%2C%20heavier%20loads%2C%20continuous%2C%20sustained%20attention%20for%20viewing%20and%20acting%20upon%20the%20aspect%20of%20approach%20signals%20%E2%80%A6%20requirement%20of%20latest%20technical%20knowledge%20and%20technique%20for%20trouble%20shooting%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20article%20considers%20the%20impact%20of%20these%20developments%20on%20the%20working%20conditions%20of%20LPs%2C%20particularly%20those%20who%20pilot%20freight%20trains.%20LPs%20are%20being%20pushed%20to%20the%20limit%20to%20cover%20the%20work%20on%20the%20railways%20%E2%80%93%20through%20lengthening%20work%20hours%2C%20continuous%20night%20shifts%20and%20reduced%20rest%20times.%20These%20conditions%20go%20a%20long%20way%20in%20explaining%20the%20recent%20spate%20of%20fatal%20railway%20accidents.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELonger%20work%20hours%20and%20consecutive%20night%20shifts%3A%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3EBacche%20poochenge%2C%20hamara%20baap%20hai%20kya%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%201973%2C%20the%20LRSA%20led%20a%20nationwide%20strike%20demanding%20that%20%E2%80%9Crunning%20duty%E2%80%9D%20(the%20portion%20of%20an%20LP%E2%80%99s%20shift%20in%20which%20the%20locomotive%20is%20being%20driven)%20be%20restricted%20to%20eight%20hours.%20The%20agreement%20signed%20between%20the%20Railway%20Board%20and%20the%20union%20stated%20that%20running%20staff%20will%20not%20be%20required%20to%20work%20for%20more%20than%2010%20hours%20at%20a%20stretch%2C%20and%20that%20this%20number%20would%20be%20reduced%20by%20half%20an%20hour%20every%20year%20until%20running%20time%20reached%20a%20maximum%20of%20eight%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20half%20a%20century%20later%2C%20LPs%20are%20regularly%20being%20forced%20to%20work%20shifts%20of%2012%20hours%20and%20more.%20This%20is%20despite%20the%20fact%20that%20according%20to%20the%20Railway%20Board%2C%20LPs%E2%80%99%20hours%20of%20duty%20are%20a%20maximum%20of%20nine%20hours%20running%20time%2C%20extendable%20to%2011%20hours%20in%20exceptional%20circumstances.%20To%20take%20just%20one%20example%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fincrease-in-train-accidents-worries-indian-railways%2Farticle66915585.ece%2Famp%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%20that%20more%20than%20a%20third%20of%20LPs%20in%20the%20South%20East%20Central%20Railway%20worked%20more%20than%2012%20hours%20in%20March%2C%20April%20and%20the%20first%20half%20of%20May%20this%20year.%20And%20LPs%20are%20systematically%20being%20forced%20to%20work%20these%20hours%20on%20pain%20of%20punishment%20%E2%80%93%20LRSA%20officials%20claims%20there%20are%20%3Cem%3Ehundreds%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20cases%20in%20which%20LPs%20have%20been%20officially%20penalised%20for%20not%20agreeing%20to%20work%20beyond%20their%20stipulated%20working-hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EConsecutive%20night%20shift%20duty%20has%20also%20been%20extended%20(night%20working%20is%20defined%20as%20working%20between%2010%20pm%20and%206%20am).%20LPs%20today%20claim%20that%20working%20five%20or%20six%20consecutive%20night%20shifts%20has%20become%20routine.%20This%20is%20despite%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20HPC%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Failrsa.com%2Fassets%2Fdocuments%2Fhpc_report_2.pdf%5C%22%3Erecommended%3C%2Fa%3E%20LPs%20work%20at%20most%20two%20nights%20in%20a%20row%2C%20citing%20an%20Indian%20Railways%20Design%20and%20Standards%20Organisation%20study%2C%20%3Cem%3EPsycho-Technology%20on%20Indian%20Railways%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20found%20that%20working%20on%20a%20second%20consecutive%20night%20shift%20has%20been%20found%20to%20dampen%20mental%20alertness%2C%20making%20drivers%20vulnerable%20to%20operational%20lapses.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnd%20LPs%20must%20often%20work%20a%20series%20of%2012-hour%20days%20and%20night%20shifts%20while%20being%20away%20from%20their%20homes%20for%20up%20to%20three%20days%20at%20a%20stretch%2C%20with%20eight%20rather%20than%20the%20usual%2016-hour%20breaks%20between%20shifts.%20During%20these%20spells%20of%20%E2%80%9Coutstation%20duty%E2%80%9D%2C%20LPs%20live%20in%20dormitory-style%20%E2%80%9Crunning%20rooms%E2%80%9D%20which%20are%20not%20conducive%20to%20the%20good%20and%20uninterrupted%20sleep%20that%20they%20require.%20For%20instance%2C%2025%20beds%20for%20railwaymen%20are%20often%20put%20in%20one%20dormitory%20%E2%80%93%20since%20different%20crews%20have%20different%20working%20times%2C%20when%20one%20crew%20awakes%20for%20work%2C%20the%20sleep%20of%20all%20the%20others%20is%20disturbed.%20These%2072-hour%20working%20periods%20are%20sometimes%20worked%20with%20just%20a%2016-hour%20break%20between%20them%20%E2%80%93%20giving%20LPs%20only%2016%20hours%20at%20home%20with%20their%20family%20in%20six%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20about%20the%20impact%20of%20this%20on%20family%20life%2C%20an%20LP%20I%20interviewed%20replied%3A%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3EBacche%20poochenge%2C%20hamara%20baap%20hai%20kya%20%3C%2Fem%3E(Our%20children%20will%20ask%2C%20do%20we%20have%20a%20father)%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25132053%2F288A2183.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25132053%2F288A2183.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25132053%2F288A2183-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25132053%2F288A2183-1024x683.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-675199%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAll%20India%20Loco%20Running%20Staff%20Association%E2%80%99s%20meeting%20of%20around%20500%20running%20staff%20near%20Jantar%20Mantar%20protesting%20against%20the%20monetisation%20of%20the%20Railways%20and%20to%20seek%20remedies%20to%20the%20grievances%20faced%20by%20running%20staff.%20Photo%3A%20Zaen%20Alkazi%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EShrinking%20rest%20periods%3A%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CSola%20ghante%20kha%20gae%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20single%2C%20continuous%20and%20night%20shifts%20have%20lengthened%2C%20changes%20to%20railway%20housing%20and%20manipulations%20of%20the%20periodical%20break%20periods%20LPs%20are%20entitled%20to%20have%20been%20chipping%20away%20at%20their%20time%20for%20rest.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAlthough%20LPs%20should%20have%20a%2016-hour%20break%20between%20shifts%20at%20their%20home%20stations%2C%20they%20cannot%20properly%20relax%20in%20these%20periods.%20They%20must%20always%20be%20ready%20to%20report%20to%20work%20%E2%80%93%20they%20are%20only%20given%20two%20hours%20to%20report%20for%20duty%2C%20sometimes%20even%20less%20%E2%80%93%20and%20if%20they%20are%20even%20five%20minutes%20late%20to%20work%20penalised%C2%A0and%20their%20pay%20and%20increments%20are%20cut.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20LPs%20claim%20that%20due%20to%20the%20mismanagement%20of%20rosters%20after%20signing%20on%20for%20work%2C%20they%20are%20sometimes%20kept%20waiting%20for%20up%20to%20four%20hours%20while%20the%20train%20is%20being%20prepared%2C%20a%20period%20when%20they%20could%20be%20home%20and%20resting.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThese%2016-hour%20rest%20periods%20are%20curtailed%20by%20the%20fact%20that%20many%20railway%20workers%20who%20used%20to%20live%20in%20railway%20colonies%20a%20short%20distance%20from%20their%20home%20stations%20now%20live%20at%20a%20distance%20from%20them%20and%20must%20commute%20to%20and%20from%20work.%20Over%20the%20years%2C%20LPs%20report%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.staffnews.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F08%2FFinal-Minutes-PNMNFIR-15_16-July-2022.pdf%5C%22%3Econditions%20in%20railway%20colonies%20have%20been%20deteriorating%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20issue%20railway%20unions%20have%20raised%20complaints%20about.%20To%20take%20just%20one%20example%2C%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20large%20Tughlakabad%20Railway%20Colony%20which%20is%20connected%20by%20overbridge%20to%20Tughlakabad%20station%20(an%20important%20goods%20terminus%2C%20being%20situated%20next%20to%20the%20Container%20Corporation%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20Inland%20Container%20Depot%2C%20advertised%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fconcorindia.co.in%2Fterminal.aspx%3Ftid%3D119%26id%3D16%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CIndia%E2%80%99s%20biggest%20dry%20port%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E)%2C%20is%20situated%20just%20a%20few%20hundred%20metres%20from%20the%20enormous%20Okhla%20landfill%20rubbish%20heap.%20Here%20many%20buildings%20are%20in%20an%20advanced%20state%20of%20disrepair%2C%20while%20many%20rooms%20are%20clearly%20long%20deserted.%20In%20recent%20years%2C%20rather%20than%20live%20in%20these%20conditions%2C%20some%20LPs%20have%20moved%20out%20to%20privately%20rented%20accommodation%20or%20started%20paying%20EMIs%20on%20flats.%20This%20means%20they%20now%20have%20to%20commute%2C%20sometimes%20for%20over%20an%20hour%2C%20to%20and%20from%20work%2C%20further%20curtailing%20their%20rest%20period.%20This%20is%20apart%20from%20the%20fact%20that%20in%20some%20instances%2C%20LPs%20have%20long%20lived%20far%20from%20their%20%E2%80%98home%20stations%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20for%20instance%2C%20living%20in%20Pune%2C%20while%20their%20%E2%80%98home%20station%E2%80%99%20is%20at%20Chhatrapati%20Shivaji%20Maharaj%20Terminus%20in%20Mumbai.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ELPs%20are%20also%20entitled%20to%20%E2%80%9Cperiodical%20rest%E2%80%9D%20of%20either%20four%20periods%20of%2030%20hours%20each%20(120%20hours)%20or%20five%20periods%20of%2022%20hours%20each%20(110%20hours)%20in%20a%20month.%20LRSA%20officials%20claim%20that%20this%20is%20called%20%E2%80%9Cperiodical%E2%80%9D%20rather%20than%20%E2%80%9Cweekly%E2%80%9D%20rest%20to%20remove%20any%20obligation%20on%20the%20part%20of%20the%20Indian%20Railways%20to%20give%20LPs%20time%20off%20every%20seven%20days.%20Nevertheless%2C%20these%20rest%20periods%20are%20insufficient%20for%20LPs%20to%20get%20proper%20breaks%20from%20work%20%E2%80%93%20the%20HPC%20itself%20recommended%20four%20periods%20of%2040%20hours%20(160%20hours)%20break%20a%20month%20to%20ensure%20proper%20rest%20for%20LPs.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20even%20these%20short%20periodical%20break%20periods%20have%20been%20manipulated%20to%20shorten%20them%20even%20further.%20Clearly%2C%20after%20their%20last%20shift%20before%20a%20periodical%20break%2C%20LPs%20should%20get%20their%20regular%2016%20hours%20off%20and%20then%20begin%20their%20period%20of%2030%20or%2022%20hours%20periodical%20break%2C%20giving%20them%20a%20total%20break%20of%2046%20(30%2B16)%20or%2038%20(22%2B16)%20hours%20rest.%20But%20in%20practice%2C%20the%20railway%20administration%20does%20not%20add%20any%20time%20to%20the%2030%20or%2022%20hours%20rest.%20These%2016%20hours%20are%20disregarded%20by%20the%20railway%20management%20%E2%80%93%20as%20one%20LRSA%20official%20put%20it%3A%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3ESola%20ghante%20kha%20gae%20%3C%2Fem%3E(They%20ate%2016%20hours).%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20means%20that%20LPs%20get%20only%20(22%20x%205%20x%2012%20or%2030%20x%204%20x%2012)%2055-60%2024-hour%20rest%20periods%20off%20over%20a%20year.%20In%20comparison%2C%20K.C.%20James%2C%20secretary%20general%20of%20AILRSA%2C%20has%20calculated%20in%20his%20book%20%3Cem%3EPlight%20of%20Locomen%3A%20A%20Study%20on%20Grievances%20of%20Loco%20Running%20Staff%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20staff%20with%20Saturday-Sunday%20rest%20get%20147%20days%20of%20rest%20in%20a%20year%2C%20or%20around%20%3Cem%3Etwo%20and%20a%20half%20times%3C%2Fem%3E%20more%20than%20LPs.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20LRSA%20officials%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faifap.org.in%2F9954%2F%5C%22%3Epoint%20out%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Railways%E2%80%99%20%3Cem%3EReport%20of%20Task%20Force%20on%20Safety%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2017)%20found%20that%20the%20majority%20of%20%E2%80%98Signal%20Passed%20At%20Danger%E2%80%99%20(SPAD)%20cases%20happened%20%3Cem%3Eafter%3C%2Fem%3E%20home%20rest%2C%20proving%20that%20home%20rest%20is%20inadequate.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisaster%20waiting%20to%20happen%3A%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3ENeend%20nahin%20aayegi%20kya%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20fatigue%20caused%20by%20long%20working%20hours%2C%20continuous%20night%20shifts%2C%20and%20lack%20of%20good%20and%20accumulated%20sleep%20are%20major%20factors%20which%20lead%20to%20railway%20accidents.%20As%20one%20clearly%20underslept%20LP%2C%20angry%20and%20agitated%20after%20describing%20the%20long%20shifts%20of%20railway%20workers%20replied%20when%20I%20asked%20him%20about%20the%20experience%20of%20piloting%20a%20train%20after%20inadequate%20sleep%3A%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3EHam%20insaan%20hai%20%E2%80%A6%20hame%20neend%20nahin%20aayegi%20kya%20%3C%2Fem%3E(We%20are%20human%2C%20will%20we%20not%20feel%20sleepy)%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20consider%20some%20examples%20of%20accidents%20from%20the%20previous%20decade%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20May%2022%2C%202012%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Failrsa.com%2Fassets%2Fdocuments%2Fhpc_report_2.pdf%5C%22%3EHampi%20Express%3C%2Fa%3E%20crashed%20into%20a%20stationary%20freight%20train%20at%20Penukonda%2C%20Andhra%20Pradesh%2C%20killing%2025%20people.%20The%20LP%20had%20recently%20worked%20seven%20straight%20nights%20in%20a%20row.%20Moreover%2C%20out%20of%20the%2028%20trips%20he%20had%20piloted%20in%20the%20previous%20month%2C%2023%20involved%20night%20working%2C%20including%20three%20periods%20of%20seven%2C%20five%20and%20three%20continuous%20nights.%20Instead%20of%20four%20periods%20of%20periodical%20rests%2C%20he%20had%20only%20had%20three.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20September%2030%2C%202014%2C%20the%20Manduadih-Lucknow%20Krishak%20Express%20collided%20with%20the%20Lucknow-Barauni%20Express%20near%20Gorakhpur%20Cantonment%20yard%20killing%2012%20people.%20LPs%20interviewed%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Flucknow%2F13-killed-50-hurt-in-gorakhpur-train-collision%2Farticleshow%2F44042155.cms%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ETimes%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20time%20stated%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20get%20less%20than%2010%20hours%20of%20rest%20after%2012-14%20hour%20shifts%20%E2%80%A6%20Sometimes%20we%20end%20up%20doing%20double%20shifts.%E2%80%9D%20All%20Indian%20Railwaymen%E2%80%99s%20Federation%20officials%20claimed%20that%20there%20was%20a%2025-26%25%20shortage%20of%20LPs%20and%20in%20some%20instances%2C%20LPs%20were%20working%2023-hour%20shifts%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20August%208%2C%202019%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faifap.org.in%2F9954%2F%5C%22%3EVeppagunta%20station%20of%20the%20Chennai-Renigunta%20section%20of%20Southern%20Railway%3C%2Fa%3Es%2C%20an%20inter-departmental%20inquiry%20into%20a%20SPAD%20case%20found%20that%20it%20was%20induced%20by%20long%20hours%20of%20work.%20The%20LP%20had%20been%20working%2014-hour%20shifts%20and%20an%20average%20of%20140%20hours%2Ffortnight%20against%20the%20statutory%20limit%20of%20104%20hours%2Ffortnight%20for%20the%20previous%20five%20fortnights.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%202023%2C%20the%20overwork%20of%20LPs%20seems%20to%20be%20reaching%20a%20point%20where%20accidents%20are%20becoming%20a%20regular%20occurrence%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20April%2019%2C%202023%2C%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faifap.org.in%2F9954%2F%5C%22%3ESinghpur%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20two%20coal-loaded%20freight%20trains%20collided%20and%20hit%20a%20third.%20One%20LP%20was%20instantly%20killed%2C%20while%20five%20other%20LPs%20were%20seriously%20injured.%20The%20LP%20Rajesh%20Prasad%20Gupta%20and%20ALP%20had%20passed%2014-15%20hours%20of%20duty%20at%20a%20stretch%20when%20the%20accident%20took%20place.%20The%20Commissioner%20of%20Railway%20Safety%20Report%20found%20that%20the%20LP%20was%20most%20likely%20in%20a%20daze%20or%20%E2%80%9Cmicro-sleep%E2%80%9D%20due%20to%20exhaustion%20and%20made%20no%20conscious%20effort%20to%20apply%20the%20brakes%20%E2%80%93%20hence%20the%20collision%20took%20place%20at%20speed%2C%20at%2056%20km%2Fhour.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F08104615%2FUntitled-design-34-2.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F08104615%2FUntitled-design-34-2.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F08104615%2FUntitled-design-34-2-300x169.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F08104615%2FUntitled-design-34-2-1024x576.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-657098%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22675%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20site%20of%20the%20Balasore%20train%20clash.%20Photo%3A%20Video%20screengrab%20from%20Twitter%2F%40RailMinIndia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20June%202%2C%202023%20near%20Bahanaga%20Bazaar%20Railway%20Station%2C%20Odisha%20a%20passenger%20train%20hit%20a%20stationary%20goods%20train%2C%20the%20fallout%20of%20which%20hit%20a%20third%20train.%20At%20least%20288%20people%20were%20killed%2C%20making%20it%20India%E2%80%99s%20worst%20train%20accident%20since%201995.%20The%20LP%20Gunanidhi%20Mohanty%20and%20ALP%20Hajari%20Behera%20had%20been%20on%20outstation%20duty%2C%20with%20their%20last%20rest%20being%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fst2.indiarailinfo.com%2Fkjfdsuiemjvcya3%2F0%2F7%2F1%2F7%2F5741717%2F0%2Fanexureabcof12841exp180759.pdf%5C%22%3Eoutstation%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20June%2025%2C%202023%2C%20in%20Adra%2C%20West%20Bengal%2C%20two%20goods%20trains%20collided.%20According%20to%20an%20AILRSA%20Press%20Release%20on%20July%206%2C%202023%2C%20out%20of%20the%2018%20trips%20LP%20Swarup%20Singha%20had%20completed%20in%20the%20previous%20month%2C%2014%20trips%20were%20during%20the%20night%2C%2010%20trips%20exceeded%2010%20hours%20and%20eight%20trips%20exceeded%2012%20hours.%20Out%20of%2022%20trips%20ALP%20G.S%20Kumar%20had%20completed%20in%20the%20previous%20month%2C%2017%20trips%20were%20during%20the%20night%2C%2013%20trips%20exceeded%2010%20hours%20duty%20and%20eight%20trips%20exceeded%2012%20hours%20duty.%20In%20addition%20to%20that%2C%20he%20had%20been%20forced%20to%20work%20continuously%20for%2019.56%20hours%20from%205%3A24%20am%20to%201%3A20%20am%20and%20on%20another%20occasion%2016.50%20hours%20continuously%20from%205%20pm%20to%209%3A50%20am.%20In%20this%20case%2C%20extreme%20fatigue%20and%20accumulated%20sleep%20debt%20seemed%20to%20have%20induced%20%E2%80%9Cmicro%20sleep%E2%80%9D%20in%20both%20LPs.%20Despite%20these%20gruelling%20work%20schedules%2C%20both%20Singha%20and%20Kumar%20have%20been%20blamed%20for%20the%20accident%20and%20removed%20from%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERailway%20workers%20and%20the%20unemployed%3A%20common%20interests%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20on%20the%20one%20hand%2C%20millions%20of%20Indian%20railway%20workers%20need%20more%20workers%20to%20share%20the%20existing%20work%20with.%20Railway%20workers%20are%20being%20pushed%20to%20%E2%80%93%20and%20beyond%20%E2%80%93%20the%20limit%20of%20endurance%20to%20make%20up%20for%20the%20shortfall%20in%20the%20workforce.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20millions%20of%20Indian%20youth%20who%20are%20applying%20for%20railway%20jobs%20are%20being%20denied%20them.%20For%20instance%2C%20in%20January%202019%2C%20more%20than%2012.5%20million%20youth%20applied%20for%2035%2C000%20railway%20jobs.%20The%20Railway%20board%20took%20three%20years%20to%20hold%20the%20examination%20and%20publish%20the%20results%2C%20which%20were%20full%20of%20irregularities.%20When%20the%20results%20were%20released%2C%20railway%20aspirants%20spent%20a%20week%20trying%20to%20make%20themselves%20heard%2C%20tweeting%20at%20the%20government%20in%20thousands.%20When%20this%20failed%20to%20have%20any%20effect%2C%20their%20anger%20exploded.%20On%20January%2024%2C%202022%2C%20in%20eastern%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20and%20Bihar%20thousands%20of%20unemployed%20youth%20demonstrated%20at%20railway%20stations%2C%20blocked%20tracks%20and%20set%20fire%20to%20trains%20in%20what%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Findia-news%2Fprotests-over-railway-jobs-are-a-grim-reminder-of-the-state-of-india-s-job-market-101643308438421.html%5C%22%3Eperhaps%20India%E2%80%99s%20first%20large-scale%20unemployment%20riots%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20response%2C%20the%20police%20attacked%20the%20protestors%20with%20lathis.%20The%20railway%20ministry%20threatened%20to%20ban%20the%20protestors%20from%20railway%20jobs%20for%20life.%20But%20this%20didn%E2%80%99t%20stop%20the%20protests%2C%20which%20continued%20for%20four%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20railways%20needs%20more%20workers%2C%20and%20the%20unemployed%20need%20work.%20Who%20is%20benefitting%20from%20standing%20in%20their%20way%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EZaen%20Alkazi%20is%20a%20labour%20historian%20and%20journalist.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%3C%2Ftr%3E%3C%2Ftbody%3E%3C%2Ftable%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695634258000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25131942%2F288A2416.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fpushed-to-the-limit-the-working-lives-of-indias-freight-train-drivers%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Loco%20pilots%20are%20being%20pushed%20to%20the%20limit%20to%20cover%20the%20work%20on%20the%20railways%20%E2%80%93%20through%20lengthening%20work%20hours%2C%20continuous%20night%20shifts%20and%20reduced%20rest%20times.%20These%20conditions%20go%20a%20long%20way%20in%20explaining%20the%20recent%20spate%20of%20fatal%20railway%20accidents.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A22%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fpushed-to-th