tion%E2%80%99%2C%20said%20Indian%20institutions%20were%20likely%20to%20face%20several%20issues%20in%20implementing%20this%20system.%20The%20report%20was%20tabled%20in%20both%20Houses%20of%20Parliament%20during%20the%20recently%20concluded%20special%20session%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EHindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Feducation%2Fnational-education-policy-2020-multiple-entry-multiple-exit-option-may-not-work-well-for-india-house-panel%2Farticle67341734.ece%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20the%20report%2C%20the%20panel%20said%20that%20while%20MEME%20has%20been%20successfully%20implemented%20in%20the%20West%2C%20it%20would%20be%20difficult%20to%20execute%20in%20India.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20institutions%20allow%20MEME%2C%20it%20would%20be%20very%20difficult%20for%20the%20institutions%20to%20predict%20how%20many%20students%20would%20exit%20and%20how%20many%20would%20join%20midway.%20Since%20institutions%20would%20not%20know%20the%20in-%20and%20out-traffic%2C%20it%20will%20certainly%20disturb%20the%20pupil-teacher%20ratio%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20also%20pointed%20out%20that%20uneven%20geographical%20distribution%20of%20higher%20educational%20institutions%20would%20create%20hurdles%20in%20managing%20MEME%20in%20several%20areas%2C%20mostly%20countryside.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20institutions%20have%20not%20thought%20very%20clearly%20about%20this%20problem%20and%20how%20they%20will%20resolve%20it%20when%20it%20is%20at%20their%20doorstep%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20added.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fnational-education-policy-funding-implementation-centralisation%5C%22%3EThe%20National%20Education%20Policy%20Has%20a%20Grand%20Vision%20but%20Can%E2%80%99t%20See%20Its%20Own%20Feet%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20recognising%20that%20MEME%20would%20offer%20students%20greater%20flexibility%20and%20choice%20in%20their%20educational%20pathways%2C%20the%20panel%20asked%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Feducation%2Fnational-education-policy-2020-multiple-entry-multiple-exit-option-may-not-work-well-for-india-house-panel%2Farticle67341734.ece%5C%22%3Edevelop%20comprehensive%20guidelines%20and%20a%20well-defined%20framework%20for%20MEME%20options%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20specific%20eligibility%20criteria%2C%20credit%20transfer%20mechanisms%20and%20a%20clear%20road%20map%20for%20students%20pursuing%20different%20exit%20points.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CAlso%2C%20implementation%20of%20a%20standardised%20Credit%20Accumulation%20and%20Transfer%20(CAT)%20system%20that%20allows%20students%20to%20earn%20and%20transfer%20credits%20seamlessly%20across%20institutions%20would%20facilitate%20smooth%20transitions%20between%20different%20levels%20of%20education%2C%20from%20certificate%20courses%20to%20doctoral%20programmes%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20panel%20also%20asked%20the%20Union%20education%20ministry%20to%20hold%20discussions%20with%20various%20educational%20institutions%20and%20their%20regulatory%20bodies%20to%20understand%20the%20problems%20in%20NEP%E2%80%99s%20implementation%20and%20what%20can%20be%20done%20to%20address%20these%20challenges.%20The%20committee%20has%20asked%20the%20ministry%20to%20apprise%20it%20of%20the%20findings%20after%20these%20consultations%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EHindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20report%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Feducation%2Fnational-education-policy-2020-multiple-entry-multiple-exit-option-may-not-work-well-for-india-house-panel%2Farticle67341734.ece%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMeanwhile%2C%20students%20and%20teachers%20raised%20apprehensions%20about%20the%20proposed%20exit%20and%20entry%20system.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20will%20reduce%20the%20value%20of%20one%E2%80%99s%20degree%20and%20this%20is%20a%20way%20to%20produce%20cheap%20labour%20for%20the%20job%20market.%20It%E2%80%99s%20an%20eyewash%20and%20we%20want%20the%20existing%20system%20to%20continue%2C%E2%80%9D%20Mayukh%20Biswas%2C%20general%20secretary%20of%20the%20Students%20Federation%20of%20India%20(SFI)%20was%20quoted%20by%20the%20paper%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695629751000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F24164751%2F1599px-Indian_Students_4616.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fmultiple-entry-exit-points-under-nep-unfit-for-indian-education-system-parliamentary-panel%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%E2%80%9CIf%20institutions%20allow%20multiple%20exits%2C%20it%20would%20be%20very%20difficult%20for%20the%20institutions%20to%20predict%20how%20many%20students%20would%20exit%20and%20how%20many%20would%20join%20midway%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20panel%20said%20in%20its%20report.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fmultiple-entry-exit-points-under-nep-unfit-for-indian-education-system-parliamentary-panel%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22India%20loosening%20its%20planned%20restrictions%20on%20laptop%2C%20tablet%20imports%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695623450000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-09%2F25%2Ffull%2F1695623087-6747.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Findia-loosening-its-planned-restrictions-on-laptop-tablet-imports-123092500306_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20part%20of%20the%20latest%20plan%2C%20all%20companies%20bringing%20everything%20from%20tablets%20and%20laptops%20to%20desktop%20computers%20and%20serve